WEBVTT

00:00:01.169 --> 00:00:22.170
When we think of Acts chapter 1 and verse 8, we think of this challenging assignment that the apostles were given and we can only just imagine them thinking about the other promise of power and Holy Spirit being with them, they certainly would need that to go to the most distant part of the earth.

00:00:22.170 --> 00:00:35.170
When we think back to the first century, we think of ones such as the Apostle Paul, Barnabas, Timothy and many others who literally tried to go as far as they could to reach various territories.

00:00:35.170 --> 00:00:48.170
If we take our Bibles and turn the book of Romans chapter 15 and verses 23 and 24, we see summarized here the Apostle Paul's viewpoint with regard to this.

00:00:48.170 --> 00:00:59.170
Romans 15, 23, but now I no longer have untouched territory in these regions and for many years I have long to come to you and that's the brothers in Rome.

00:00:59.170 --> 00:01:03.170
Therefore, when I journey to Spain, I hope that I will see you.

00:01:03.170 --> 00:01:08.170
So Paul was very concerned about going to untouched territories.

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:27.170
Well, in recent times we can say the same is true of Jehovah's people, whether it be the Gilead missionaries who have been sent out or other missionaries even prior to the time of Gilead being established or we think of the brothers who have moved to other countries to serve with the need as greater.

00:01:27.170 --> 00:01:37.170
Or perhaps those that have gone out to unassigned territories or helped in areas where very few people get the opportunity to hear the message.

00:01:37.170 --> 00:01:42.170
When we hear those experiences, we certainly are encouraged by them, aren't we?

00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:49.170
But perhaps we could think this morning about just one of the aspects of the history in the past.

